arXiv.abstract:
We report new constraints on flavor-changing non-standard neutrino interactions from the MINOS long-baseline experiment using $
u_{e}$ and $ ar{
u}_{e}$ appearance candidate events from predominantly $
u_{\mu}$ and $ ar{
u}_{\mu}$ beams. We used a statistical selection algorithm to separate $
u_{e}$ candidates from background events, enabling an analysis of the combined MINOS neutrino and antineutrino data. We observe no deviations from standard neutrino mixing, and thus place constraints on the non-standard interaction matter effect, $|\varepsilon_{e	au}|$, and phase, $(\delta_{CP}+\delta_{e	au})$, using a thirty-bin likelihood fit.

